If TF x can also bind with a partner y, occupancy of x depends on x binding in isolation, as before, but also binding with y as a xy heterodimer, depending on the concentration [xy] and the Kdxy of the heterodimer. At equilibrium, [xy] = [x][y]Kaxy, where Kaxy is the association constant of x and y. Thus, for x binding to a single binding site with or without cooperative binding of y, we have:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
